---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="SEO Regression" description="RankMySEO SEO regression CLI — gate preview vs production.">
  <h1>SEO regression CLI</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Opt-in CI gate that compares a candidate (preview) URL against a production baseline using
    <code>@rankmyseo/scanner</code> and config under <code>regression</code>.
  </p>

  <pre><code>npx rankmyseo-cli regression check \
  --candidate-url https://preview.example.com \
  --base-ref origin/main \
  --json</code></pre>

  <h2>Requirements</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>regression.enabled</code> + <code>regression.productionUrl</code> + <code>routeMap</code> in config</li>
    <li>Packages: <code>@rankmyseo/cli</code> (pulls scanner)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Exit codes</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Code</th>
        <th>Meaning</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>0</code></td>
        <td>Pass</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>1</code></td>
        <td>Gated findings</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>2</code></td>
        <td>Runtime / config / network error</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>
    Full guide:
    <a href="https://github.com/madebyaris/rankmyseo/wiki/SEO-Regression">Wiki → SEO Regression</a>
    · Example workflow: <code>.github/workflows/seo-regression.example.yml</code>
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
